      • getDelay

        int getDelay()
        Gets the current delay of the next spawn. This number is ever changing and gets randomized between spawns.
        Returns:
        current spawn delay

      • setDelay

        void setDelay(int delay)
        Allows delay of what to spawn to change on-the-fly. Modification of this is near-useless as delays get randomized after spawn.
        Parameters:
        delay - Set the next spawn delay.

      • getMinDelay

        int getMinDelay()
        Returns the minimum delay of the spawner. The delay between spawns is picked randomly between this and the max delay.
        Returns:
        minDelay The minimum delay for spawning.

      • setMinDelay

        void setMinDelay(int delay)
        Sets the minimum delay of the spawner. The delay between spawns is picked randomly between this and the max delay. Default is 200.
        Parameters:
        delay - The min delay value to set.

      • getMaxDelay

        int getMaxDelay()
        Returns the maximum delay of the spawner. The delay between spawns is picked randomly between this and the min delay.
        Returns:
        maxDelay The max delay value.

      • setMaxDelay

        void setMaxDelay(int delay)
        Sets the maximum delay of the spawner. The delay between spawns is picked randomly between this and the min delay. Default is 800.
        Parameters:
        delay - The max delay value to set.

      • getMaxNearbyEntities

        int getMaxNearbyEntities()
        Returns the maximum number of entities this spawner allows nearby in order to continue spawning. Any more entities and this spawner won't spawn mobs.
        Returns:
        Max number of entities allowed to continue spawning.

      • setMaxNearbyEntities

        void setMaxNearbyEntities(int entities)
        Sets the maximum number of entities this spawner allows nearby in order to continue spawning. Any more entities and this spawner won't spawn mobs. Default is 6.
        Parameters:
        entities - Value to set for max number of entities allowed to continue spawning.

      • getRequiredPlayerRange

        int getRequiredPlayerRange()

        Returns:
        the required range

      • setRequiredPlayerRange

        Parameters:
        range - the range to be set
